e you go We're sort of hoping that you'd stay, and we both know That the nights will mainly\",\"language\":\"en\",\"text_align\":\"center\",\"line_height\":1.2,\"letter_spacing\":0.0,\"wrap\":true,\"padding\":{\"top\":0.0,\"right\":0.0,\"bottom\":0.0,\"left\":0.0},\"background_opacity\":0.0,\"stroke_width\":0.0}}],\"serializer_mode\":\"v2\"}\nOutput: Return ONLY the following structure: EDIT PLAN Global Style: Audio Decision: Caption Style: Visual Style: Background Style: Segmentation Rule: Segment 1 Time: Purpose: Elements Used: Caption Decision: Visual Decision: Animation Decision: Placement Decision: Timing Events: - time: event Transition Out: Engagement Note: Segment 2 ... Repeat for all segments. Constraints: - Do NOT return JSON. - Do NOT return code. - Do NOT explain reasoning. - Use exact element ids and times whenever possible. - Keep the exact same headings every time. - Make the result easy to convert into JSON later."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "EDIT PLAN\nGlobal Style: Dynamic caption-focused short with style-driven typography and motion.\nAudio Decision: Use audio_1 from 0.000 to 30.001 as backbone at full volume.\nCaption Style: font_family=sans, font_style=italic, white base, gold inline highlights only for important words.\nVisual Style: Caption-only design test with animated entrances and no image overlays.\nBackground Style: grain_vignette with timed subtle design overlays.\nSegmentation Rule: Group transcript into 3-4 word caption blocks using mapping_json timings exactly.\nSegment 1\nTime: 0.000-30.001\nPurpose: Validate caption sync + style diversity on real song chunk mapping.\nElements Used: audio_1, caption_track_1\nCaption Decision: Important Words: feeling, flows, we're.\nCaption Decision: placement=right_lower, animation=pop, and grouped timings:\n- 10.561-12.663: \"If you want it\"\n- 12.663-14.764: \"soon, I want to\"\n- 14.764-16.866: \"know If this feeling\"\n- 16.866-18.967: \"flows both ways, it's\"\n- 18.967-21.069: \"sad to see you\"\n- 21.069-23.171: \"go We're sort of\"\n- 23.171-25.272: \"hoping that you'd stay,\"\n- 25.272-27.374: \"and we both know\"\nVisual Decision: Keep text readable and avoid clipping within 9:16 safe area.\nAnimation Decision: Animate each caption entry with chosen style and hold until next phrase.\nPlacement Decision: Use caption safe zone with translucent panel behind text.\nTiming Events:\n- time: 10.561 event: first caption appears\n- time: 30.001 event: last caption exits\nTransition Out: short fade.\nEngagement Note: Strong typography + motion variety while preserving sync accuracy."}]}
